{{year-header}}
==Early==
* '''?''' - [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] recovers from his trench fever to the degree that he can do home service. He is promoted to full lieutenant.

==February==
* '''[[14 February|14]]''' - Producer [[William Lawrence Snyder]] is born.

==November==
* '''[[2 November|2]]''' - [[Roger Lancelyn Green]], [[Inklings|Inkling]], is born.
* '''[[5 November|5]]''' - [[Alan Tilvern]], who would voice the [[Barliman Butterbur|"Innkeeper"]] in [[The Lord of the Rings (1978 film)]], is born.
* '''[[11 November|11]]''' - [[World War I|The War]] comes to an end. 
* '''?''' - Tolkien is accepted as a junior staff member of the ''New English Dictionary'', later called the ''[[Oxford English Dictionary]]''. He worked with words beginning with the letter "w".

==?==
* '''?''' - ''[[A Spring Harvest]]'', containing a foreword by [[J.R.R. Tolkien]], is published.
